cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.GR 

This paper is about using saliency maps to explain the behavior of deep reinforcement learning agents. The paper evaluates the degree to which saliency maps represent the semantics of RL environments using counterfactual analysis. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and graphics (cs.GR).
